</td><td><input type=checkbox name=preview>Preview</td><td> <input type=submit tabindex=5 value="Add Reply" class=inputbutton> </td><td><input type=button value="Spell Check" class=inputbutton onClick="var f=document.forms[0]; doSpell('EN', f.body, document.location.protocol + '//' + document.location.host + '/cgi?script=sproxy.cgi', true);"></td></tr></table></form><br><br><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevintest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kevintest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 6:13:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> Well...  My tentative thoughts (noting that I'm not the expert people with L50s are) are that yes, the evenom exploit (put on tons of env gear, put high poison on wpn, then take off gear and put on better combat gear) needs fixing.  In fact, I actually (ducks) question why envenom alone of all skills is given extra &quot;spells&quot; for +spec items and RP?  It's interesting to note that just like the envenom skill, many other skills also get no other bonus for +spec items - take paladin chants, for instance.  IMHO, either ALL spec lines of this nature need to get their new spells/effects like envenom does, or none do.  <br>
<br>
Not sure which it should be - with people already speccing based on env items giving new poisons, I'd suggest just give the other classes the same benefit, maybe.<br>
<br>
Nerfing stealth in any way would pretty much shut down both the minstrel and infiltrator - both of which (assuming stealth minstrel template) rely on stealth to get them &quot;up close and personal&quot; with their opponent.  You basically can't reduce stealth's effectiveness without really hurting those classes.<br>
<br>
Damage caps in general have to be set up so that the one-shot kill POSSIBILITY is removed.  I know that CS hits don't crit often (and it's mostly the 800 pt infil hits and 1000+ SB hits that get the bad PR and the blood boiling).  You know it.  But the player who gets hit ONE TIME by a hit like that does not.  He figures it will happen &quot;every time&quot;.  And he tells his friends, who tell their friends, etc.<br>
<br>
Fact is that one-shot kills (or kills that occur so fast that there is no time or chance to react in any way) between even cons are bad for the game.  They discourage people from trying to play, and reduce the level of skill by increasing the luck factor.<br>
<br>
Personally, my thought is that CS crits are so darn uncommon anyway that it really hurts the class exactly ZERO to remove 'em.  Leave standard CS damage alone.  But remove the wild, crazy, radical damage spikes.  From caster bolts too - they are just as bad.  One thousand point bolts should NEVER be happening.  My opinion. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only other solution is to base caster defense abilities off the high spikes of damage - which is what will likely happen otherwise.  Casters will be designed to survive 800pt CS +400pt poison strikes...  So unbuffed they'd need around 900-1000hp, or about 300 more than they get now, or maybe a bigger absorb buff.  That's a _bad_ solution though, really - because it bases the whole on the extreme hits, and thus reduces assassin effectiveness on the standard, everyday hits.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong - casters are SUPPOSED to die to assassins, almost every fight.  And they do.  Usually so fast they don't have time to blink. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The loss vs assassins should stay - the &quot;can't blink&quot; should not.<br>
<br>
Which reminds me - yes, an assassin should die vs a tank, about as often as a caster dies to an assassin.  3D's best win % vs a L50 warrior should have been maybe 5-10%.  Not 75%.  Tanks are the &quot;predator&quot; class for assassins - and are supposed to kill them with GREAT consistancy, if they find them.  And yes, he used specialized tactics - but now that Khel has so kindly published them, so can everyone else.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   No, collision is not a solution, because it's an equine lich.  Unfortunately.<br>
<br>
And 42 env with items really IS low for an infiltrator now, Khel - or should be.  A better term for 3D's template would have been &quot;suboptimal&quot;, not &quot;substandard&quot; - since it was nowhere near an optimal template for the style of fighting he was doing.  Would have been much easier in those fights if he had gone to 50 env buffed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you do the math - and assume that you are trying for a template that can &quot;kite-kill&quot; effectively - then the poison skill is actually even more important than the CS skill - and is VERY, VERY much more important than thrust.  51 buffed thrust and only 42 buffed envenom?  =P  Fifty buffed envenom is now optimal in general, btw - with the new poison buff, and the new Env items, that is NOT hard to get and VERY worth it.  IMHO.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
***  All of the above is the personal opinion of me as a player.  I have played every class in Albion to a decent level (mid+) during the course of the last 15 months of playing DAOC, so I have a decent basis on which to compare the way they play.  However - none of this should be construed as anything but the ramblings of someone bored at work.  They are ideas, and not official in any way.  I don't have a hidden agenda to demolish the Infiltrator - rather the contrary, because I enjoy playing the class.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
***  I am not &quot;sticking up&quot; for 3D's ideas, or posting against them.  I am suggesting that crucifying the guy for doing his best is probably pretty stupid.  And that flamefests directed at people who are asking for opinions and comments are pretty dumb too.  If a TL comes to the public boards (which they are never, ever required to do) to put out ideas and seek feedback, burning them at the stake is a surefire way to ensure that next time, they just make their suggestions to Mythic without asking for the comments.<br>
<br>
Kevin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevintest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kevintest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 6:21:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> Majin, what he's talking about is PAing the target, then running THROUGH them, and past, so they get no counter-attack.  Then you run off while they are trying to turn around, and you stealth.  It's possible to use said technique to kite targets that are MUCH tougher than you'd ordinarily be able to kill.<br>
<br>
Thinking about this, none of 3D's suggestions actually fix the real problem, though.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I certainly see where Khel is coming from in wishing for collisions.  That - or some other coding solution (better/faster /stick command, or ability to hit/cast on people who are &quot;inside&quot; you, maybe) - is going to be essential in fixing this, I think.  And collisions would be &quot;nice&quot; just in general.<br>
<br>
Kevin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukheldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kheldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 7:39:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> For all the casters that get annihilated by assassins.....I feel for you, I do.  Not only do I play an infiltrator, I also play a sorcerer, so I know it from both ends.  However, one thing I have recently learned (after biting through a lot of things after getting Shadowblasted) is that if I have a tank with guard, protect, and most importantly, intercept on me, and actually right next to me guarding me in a fight....no assassin can touch me.  The assassin goes for PA, the tank intercepts it, now the tank is very irritable, and squishes the sneaky kobold who is now right there for the world to see and uses him for a chew toy.  I will always ask a tank with me rvr'ing to put me on intercept and guard and stay close, from now on.  I saw it work, and I'm a believer.<br>
<br>
Now, from an infiltrator point of view, I'll reiterate all those endlessly tiresome but now infamous cliches, about how we live and work towards that ONE shot at massive damage, and hope that it is enough so that any incidental damage afterward (poison, bleeding, whatever) is enough to kill the target.  How many times have we all absolutely drilled a target (caster or other rogue), saw our poisons take, only to go up in flames when we die only to see the target healed at the last second.  We all know that happens far more than the infamous 1-shots.  What happens even more is taking someone down below 25% only to die and see them just sit down and heal by secondary intention while looking at our dead bodies.<br>
<br>
Our 1-shot kills and massive damage are infamous for the ONE reason that casters hate it because if they do not have a tank protecting them and intercepting for them, they have no idea when it's going to happen.  Casters like to see things at a distance and blast it, mez it, spindle-fold-mutilate it without ruffling their robes (I know I do), and they don't like it when someone maneuvers past their complacency and drills them for not taking precautions...and all that magical power that they use on everyone else is seeping into the ground with the casters anemic blood.  Casters have a 90%+/- solution in protecting themselves, they just have to do it.  The only people that we as assassins can hit so hard are casters and other rogues...and you don't hear too many rogues complaining in comparison (and Bile 1-shots me about 1:3 times he finds me due to the level difference and him being an SB).  <br>
<br>
Stealth at high levels should be damned hard to penetrate.  I don't want increased Detect Hidden range...I want it smaller, if anything for those assassins looking for me, if my stealth is better.  I think the way envenom is done needs to be fixed or changed, but giving a 'free lunch' for higher poison use because of items is not a good way to go in the first place.  There is no way in hell anyone should be able to put on items just to apply higher poisons, then remove the items and still proc the poisons. (we had a nice little argument over this previously...this doesn't work on Pendragon, and doesn't on 'some' servers, but has been proven to work on a couple of others...so it's a bug and isn't even the same on all servers.  On Pendragon, you must wear the item to both apply the poison to the weapon and to be able to proc it in combat).  <br>
<br>
Finally, I don't think the chance of a critical hit is unbalancing, even on PA.  Does it suck? Yep, if you're on the receiving end of it.  But we never complain unless we're on the receiving end.  Casters (and even light in the butt rogues) all have a means to protect themselves, they just have to make use of the tools.  <br>
<br>
Reducing CS damage in any way means fubaring the whole assassin concept in the game...because if we cannot kill in just a few seconds up to an even con caster or other rogue, then we're surely dead due to &quot;excess iron in the diet&quot; from all the irritated tanks, or a bad case of heartburn thanks of the friendly neighborhood caster if we are seen for more than 3-4 seconds tops.  IF our CS damage is reduced in any manner, then MUCH must be done to make up for how easily we die, because we die just about as easily in melee as a caster (and at high level with the new absorption spells, they have our equal in armor, 10%).  That means an entire revamping of all 3 assassin classes, and personally, I don't want to go back to October when we couldn't even kill low blues, and start over.  <br>
<br>
There has to be a better way.  For whatever reason, 3dknight is jumping the gun without exploring any options and going for the nerf now, and THAT is what has me irritated at him, along with him pushing so hard for this that he made the mistake of presuming himself to know more about assassins in general than everyone else, and not even asking for input prior to now. (Along with this, a disagreement with Pendragon infiltrators pretty much as a group, wherein we were told how we had been consulted and asked our opinions, and when we talked to each other, we found out that in fact, we weren't.  hmmm, that tends to tick people off. i.e. having it said &quot;I talk to Pendragon infiltrators all the time&quot; and then when we all talk to each other, every last one of us of an age that can rvr, and find out that isn't true, well, it makes us a wee bit upset at our class team leader).<br>
<br>
So many times classes have had huge, nasty changes made because of jumping the gun, so let's not jump it, and work on real solutions IF there is a real problem.  Just because a caster is too stupid to ask his tanks to put intercept on doesn't mean his stupidity should get assassins nerfed.  Do I think 3dknight is a complete idiot? No, I don't.  I haven't disagreed with him very often, and I know he's worked hard and was instrumental in getting infiltrators where they are now, a fun but fragile class that is a challenge to play, and an art to play well.  However, in his haste to avoid Mythic's normal approach of waving the nerf missile ('bat' my ass, it's a missile.  Come on, they don't take nor have the time to be gradual about anything...no game company does...they fix things, then they overfix, then they try to go back again).  Let's not break what I don't believe is broken.  Teach the casters that they have tools to protect themselves, and after they use them a couple of times and they work, then maybe the keening, tearing of robes and gnashing of teeth might just end without me having to uninstall this game.  Fix the envenom problem (make people 'have' to put in the points to use the best poisons), fix the fluctuations in stealth (far too easy for a caster to catch you coming in unless you come in fast), and show the casters the 'light' of intercept.  If there is STILL a problem after all this, then start digging for solutions, not just nerfing something arbitrary.<br>
<br>
