Let me counterpoint a bit:<br>
1) Casters in general don't ask for guard, protect, intercept in RvR.  In PvE, cleric types get most of this attention, and casters are not used to thinking to ask for it (I know - they need to LEARN!).  Also, in RvR using intercept means sticking REALLY close to a tank - and the tanks are usually trying to rush headlong into the fray.  Ironically, some of my best fights (as a caster) have been when I sat RIGHT on a tank's coattails, waited till he engaged a target, and then proceeded to nuke the **** out of it.  Plus, for some odd reason the best theurgist template more closely resembles a thane in fighting style than a caster anyway (go figure that one out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  So - casters need to get the word out.  The effectiveness of these tactics is, simply put, virtually unknown.<br>
<br>
2) Our top guild infil - on Galahad - regularly takes out SOLO yellow con anythings.  That's right - anything.  Now, he's in top-flight gear, and I've seen him in action, his play is simply superb (he's a lot better at the sneaky stuff than me!).  But he has absolutely no trouble at all with light (read: low hit point) tanks, and only moderate trouble with heavy tanks.  He says healer-types are a PITA, but doable in emergancies.  He's got a better than 50% win ratio vs every class.<br>
<br>
Now - the question is, are assassins SUPPOSED to win vs anyone and everyone?  In an ideal game, my thought would be that any class could beat any other class if the player was more skilled.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Mythic's view on this though is that tanks should trump rogues - so there shoud not be a positive win % vs tanks for rogue classes.  Right now, there is.  Our guild's tanks fear archers and assassins more than they fear other tanks.  I think only Hib casters rank up there (stupid stuns! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  Part of that, though, is the surprise factor.  Stealthers can always hit when you LEAST want them to, which gets annoying.  It's part of the fun of being sneaky. =)<br>
