Selvarr, good questions:<br>
Was it a &quot;cheesy tactic&quot;?  Maybe - but expect to see more of it now that it's out.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Works great - superb even - on any solo target.  Warrior had a hard time shrugging off 550pts (avg 265pt infil PA + 300pts poison) of damage!  And a snare poison.  By the time the snare was wearing off, the infil can be circling for another hit.  It's sort of like a dance - if the infil can make 2-3 passes before help comes, he wins.  If help comes before the kill, the warrior lives and the infil vanishes.<br>
<br>
Problem with walking around in autoattack mode (and yah, Warrior was trying his darndest to win I gather - best chance he had was if he could stun) is that the PA was executed in such a way that by the time Warrior-computer reads the attack, the infil was already INSIDE the warrior - and thus unhittable (this works GREAT on casters too, btw).  Infil continues moving out the back side, and while warrior is trying to whirl he's sprinting away to engage stealth.  How long do 3 back-to-back DoT poisons take?  That is how long the tank has to get help before he dies.<br>
<br>
Funny thing is, our guild's infil doesn't even do this.  He picks a light tank.  Lines up PA.  PAs for 300ish, or a bit more under some circumstances.  Poisons for 400.  That's 700 damage right there...  Light tanks only have a couple hundred more than that (about 900-1000 base, plus another 200ish for item buffs).  Engage a 2nd DoT partway through the fight, and you have a really dead light tank.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think they should keep it in perspective that they aren't playing on a live server&quot; - actually, most of us do.  I play Galahad, and Bors if I'm in a &quot;hibbie&quot; mood.  Most of the other TLs also play a live server as their prime - or used to, not sure now with all the new TLs we have.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We head to Pendragon to test under somewhat more controlled conditions, is all.<br>
