Funny thing is, I agree with Khel here on _almost_ everything.  I agree on envenom - the bug w/ use of poisons without wearing the gear needs to get fixed.  Envenom being the ONLY skill that grants new effects for gear and RP needs to be looked at; other classes could use this too, Paladin being notable for it, and it just doesn't seem _right_ that one class gets this bene but none others do, does it?  Heck, if you think about it a minute - envenom is very akin to a caster's spell line - yet no caster gets new spells for +spec items.  Perhaps they should?  I'd always rather see boosts than nerfs, where it's possible.<br>
<br>
I disagree on the CS _critical hit_.  I DO agree that base CS needs to be left the heck alone!  An infil has a hard enough time without reducing that even one hp.  But - crit hits on CS seem to be generating 90% of the complaints, and give assassins just about nothing IMHO.  Bottom line is, if they are rare - then they are unreliable, hence useless to the class; and if they are useless, then why not remove the major complaint people have?  If they are common, then they are valuable - but if they are common enough to be critical to the class, then they are overpowered.<br>
