Now let me put it in terms you may understand, or may not depending on your ancestry and IQ. <br>
<br>
In this game, and in reality, infantry troops definition and mission in life is &quot;to seek out, close with, and destroy the enemy, in order to take and hold ground&quot;.  Nothing is harder in warfare than to remove entrenched infantry from a well-prepared position.<br>
<br>
Because, in Mythic's extreme shortsightedness, this game does not have collision detection, the infantry, i.e. all non-stealth classes who use a hand held weapon as their primary method of attack, have no means to take and hold ground in the classic sense, and protect valuable assets like healers and casters.  However, Mythic has input 'guard', 'protect' and 'intercept' as a very narrow but effective means for valuable assets to be protected.  All 3 work well in pve, and intercept works well in pvp.<br>
<br>
You cannot take and hold any ground, whatsoever, because your enemies can run right through you, or control/kill you from range.  No heroic 'shield to shield' stands can be made because of this.  You have to make use of the tools you have.  Screaming hordes of people rushing en masse down upon the enemy only works when the horde outnumbers their enemy by an extremely large amount, and in Hollywood and Starcraft.  Well thought out strategy and sound tactics are what wins battles most often, even in games.  I've seen tanks protect casters and healers to the point that that fact alone carried the battle for them.  I also see a lot of high level tanks get massacred as they tried the &quot;screaming horde&quot; approach, then they bitch about it when waiting for a rez or releasing. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukheldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kheldor</A> at: 4/18/02 10:49:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 10:26:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply to Kevintest and Smith</span><hr size=1> Lucidus, stop talking theory.  Has anyone on the boards complained about being killed in by level 20-somethings wielding lifebane?  No one has.  It's not a problem until people complain about it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulucidusdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LucidusDAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 11:53:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezb